<paragraph id="533336B3E44EFFF4FF4960B37AD8FEF9" blockId="32.[151,1436,151,315]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E44EFFF4FF4960B37BFCFF51" bold="true" box="[199,465,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species belongs in the 
<taxonomicName id="948C4D30E44EFFF4FC8960B37957FF51" box="[775,890,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xylophilus">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E44EFFF4FC8960B37957FF51" box="[775,890,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">xylophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The male can be separated from all other members of the genus by the combination of the following characters: acrostichals present; anal point short; and basal projection of inferior volsella long, digitiform, bearing long lamellae reaching the apex of the inferior volsella.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B966538E44EFFF6FF4961067873FD4B" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="533336B3E44EFFF4FF4961067F38FEDA" blockId="32.[151,1436,151,315]" box="[199,1301,290,315]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E44EFFF4FF4961067B63FEDA" bold="true" box="[199,334,290,315]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Latin 
<taxonomicName id="948C4D30E44EFFF4FE5461067859FEDA" authorityName="Pinho &amp; Mendes &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="2013" box="[474,628,290,315]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curticaudatus">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E44EFFF4FE5461067859FEDA" box="[474,628,290,315]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">curticaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning short tailed, referring to the size of the anal point.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E44EFFF4FF1961437B37FE61" blockId="32.[151,1436,359,695]" box="[151,282,359,384]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E44EFFF4FF4961AE79A8FE27" blockId="32.[151,1436,359,695]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E44EFFF4FF4961AE7B29FE42" bold="true" box="[199,260,394,419]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Male</emphasis>
(n = 4–5). Total length 2.18–2.71, 
<quantity id="94749B56E44EFFF4FD0561AE78DFFE43" box="[651,754,394,419]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.52" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="2.52">2.52 mm</quantity>
. Wing length 1.06–1.12, 
<quantity id="94749B56E44EFFF4FB8561AE7E5CFE43" box="[1035,1137,394,419]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.09" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="1.09">1.09 mm</quantity>
. Total length / wing length 2.07–2.61, 2.32. Wing length / length of profemur 1.93–2.15, 2.00.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E44EFFF4FF4961EB7F2BFE09" blockId="32.[151,1436,359,695]" box="[199,1286,463,488]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E44EFFF4FF4961EB7B64FE09" box="[199,329,463,488]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head and abdomen pale; thorax pale, with vittae and scutum stramineous. Legs pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E44EFFF4FF4961D67E13FD92" blockId="32.[151,1436,359,695]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E44EFFF4FF4961D67B26FDEA" box="[199,267,498,523]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Head.</emphasis>
AR 1.00–1.32, 1.25; ultimate flagellomere 460–519, 508 µm long. Inner vertical 1; outer verticals 3–4, 4; postorbitals 3–4, 4. Clypeus with 10–13, 11 setae. Tentorium 71–116, 96 µm long; 23–35, 30 µm wide. Stipes 121–129 (3) µm long. Palpomere lengths (in µm): 25–46, 35; 28–46, 35; 99–129, 114; 124–167, 149; 182–233, 202. Third palpomere with 3–4, 4 sensillae subapically, longest 13–15, 14 µm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E44EFFF4FF4962597AFBFD56" blockId="32.[151,1436,359,695]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E44EFFF4FF4962597B35FD77" box="[199,280,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="CBB72A36E44EFFF4FEA862597B57FD77" box="[294,378,637,662]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–53" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[248,1326,237,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-63@33.[226,1360,197,1860]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 49–53. Beardius curticaudatus sp. n., male. 49—wing; 50—thorax; 51—hypopygium, lateral view; 52—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 53—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270918/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Scutal tubercle absent. Dorsocentrals 7–9, 8; acrostichals 7–8, 8; prealars 2. Scutellum with 6 setae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="07F3663BE44EFFF4FF1966D67B0DF8A4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270916" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5270916" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270916/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" startId="32.[151,264,1778,1800]" targetBox="[274,1312,759,1742]" targetPageId="32">
